**Sysinfo**
- VSCode Version: 1.2.1
- OS Version:  Win10

**Steps to Reproduce**
1.  Use any defined function
2.  Observe no syntax highlighting

**Example**

```
const thisFunction = () => {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        resolve('Works!')
    })
}

thisFunction.then((res) => {
    console.log(res)
}).catch(console.error)
```

I would expect there to be highlighting on the function call block, but VS code just colors the entire thing as white, as shown here (the syntax is set to JS):
![2016-07-01 14_48_04- untitled-1 - wandbook - visual studio code](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7088852/16519904/5b6f9a62-3f9d-11e6-9858-4b4662392517.png)
